title: For Sale/Trade:   Romanian PSL with extras POSP 8X42 and 5 Magazines
location: East Colorado Springs, Colorado Springs, Colorado
postcontent: This is a Romanian made PSL.  Not one made from spare parts in the US. All numbers match. The rifle features a last shot bolt hold open.  The barrel is hard chrome lined and is immaculate. It still has the bayonette lug that works for those who care. This is one of the few that made it in without it being ground off. It has been shot about 300 times. It comes with 5X 10 round original magazines!  This PSL has been Duracoated in FDE as well as the magazines. A Tapco double hook trigger has been installed and it has a very smooth and light pull. The scope is a Belarus made 8x42 POSP with an illuminated reticle graduated for the 7.62x54R past 1000M. It is battery powered and runs on common 2032 batteries. The mount is a Kalinka high mount so you can use the iron sights rapidly if needed. These PSL's are getting harder to find and the prices will only go up just like the SVD's and TIGR rifles back in the day. The stock is a Rhineland Arms Walnut and it has a longer length of pull and it is much better quality than the original. Text REDACTED or email.

-Bestop seats front and rear

title: For Sale/Trade:  Akdal 1919 AR-15 Look-Alike, 2 5 round magazines, 1 10 round magazine
postcontent:
This shotgun is approaching it's manufacturer's recommended 100 round break in period. (about 75-ish rounds of all types of loads) It is becoming more and more fun to shoot. This includes 10 round mag that already had the alteration done on it from the manufacturer.

The Akdal MKA 1919 is a gas operated, semi-automatic shotgun that resembles the M16 rifle and mimics the layout and placement of some of the controls. It was created by Turkish company Akdal Arms. The MKA 1919 uses a conventional gas-operated action which is located around the support tube that runs below the barrel. The return spring is also located around the same support tube which is concealed by an enlarged polymer handguard. The MKA 1919 barrel can be quickly removed from upper receiver. To charge the shotgun, the charging handle on the receiver must be pulled. The upper receiver is manufactured from an aluminum alloy while the lower receiver, along with pistol grip and shoulder stock, is manufactured as one piece from impact-resistant polymer. Akdal MKA 1919 semi-automatic shotgun has a 5 round detachable box magazine. It has a bolt release identical in location and function to the one on the M16. Manual safety also duplicates M16-style being located on the left side of the receiver above the pistol grip.[1] Standard sights include a front post installed on the M16-style removable base and a detachable M16A2-style carrying handle with built-in diopter sight. On the upper receiver, an integral Picatinny rail can be placed which will accept detachable carrying handle or optional red-dot or other optical sight attachments.

title: For Sale:  class 2 ar-15 m16 drilling jig
postcontent: I contracted a machine shop to make these m16 drilling jigs and they are made to a very high quality. They are made using heat treated a2 tool steel that is 38-42RC hardness so these will last a very long time. The materials alone were very expensive but since my friend is a cnc machinest i got a huge break. a2 steel is a very difficult steel to machine and each part took 1.5 hours of labor. the hole locations were made using a GI colt m16a1 receiver that was placed in a CMM (co-ordinate measuring machine) and machined to a tolerance of +- .0005 since this jig has 2 holes (take down and selector hole) it places the sear pin hole exactly where it should be and takes out the guess work and room for error that one hole jigs leave. if your receivers rear take down and selector hole is to spec as it shold be this jig puts the sear pin hole 100% where it needs to go. each jig was cross checked for correct hole locations and when pinned up to a gi m16 the holes lined up perfect. all nfa rules apply. shipping is included
